Brandeis University Offers CARL UnCover Gateway
 
The January/February 1990 issue of On CARL, the newsletter of the
Colorado Alliance of Research Libraries, indicates that the
Libraries of Brandeis University are offering their users access
to both the CARL UnCover database and the Boston Library
Consortium's Union List of Serials via an Internet link on the
campus LAN.  Boston College also provides access to the UnCover
database.
 
 
Brodart Produces Large CD-ROM Union Catalog
 
Brodart Automation announces that it has produced a CD-ROM union
catalog for the Commonwealth of Virginia that contains 3.3 million
unique titles.  The CD-ROM union catalog, called CAVALIR, is
contained on five CD-ROM disks, and it is being distributed to 220
libraries across the state.
 
